          "id": "tldr:2023-01-30:o006",
          "order": 1,
          "title": "CARBONYL",
          "summary": "Carbonyl is a Chromium-based browser built to run in a terminal. It supports running almost all Web APIs, including WebGL, WebGPU, audio and video playback, and animations. Carbonyl starts up in less than a second and runs at 60 FPS with 0% CPU usage when idle. It is compatible with safe-mode consoles and can even be used through SSH. Carbonyl has only been tested on Linux and macOS.",
          "url": "https://github.com/fathyb/carbonyl",
